The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for named entity recognition, which are typically covered under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of neural networks and deep learning architectures also suggests a possible fit under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of lexicons and partial matching, which could potentially fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and named entity recognition (cs.NE) sub-categories.
